                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[73]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from"
                            >Fish</persName>, Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Pierrepont</persName>, district attorney.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-06-29">
                        <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 29, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards Pierrepont</hi>, <hi
                        rend="italic">United States District Attorney,<lb/>No</hi>. 41 <hi
                        rend="italic">Chambers street, and at</hi> 103 <hi rend="italic">Fifth
                        avenue, New York:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>By order of the President, the captured vessels, with the men engaged in the
                    unlawful expedition, will be taken to the navy-yard at Brooklyn, and there put
                    under the charge and control of the officer in command of the yard, who is
                    empowered by the President, by virtue of the power for that purpose in him
                    vested, to employ such part of the naval forces of the United States as are
                    under his command, for the purpose of taking possession of and detaining such
                    ship or vessel for the purposes intended by law.</p>
                <p>By order of the President:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
